Key);\n        BCFrodoPublicKey restoredKey = deserialize(serializedKey);\n\n        assertThat(restoredKey).isEqualTo(publicKey);\n        assertThat(restoredKey.hashCode()).isEqualTo(publicKey.hashCode());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"Frodo\");\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getFormat()).isEqualTo(\"X.509\");\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getEncoded()).isEqualTo(publicKey.getEncoded());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getParameterSpec().getName())\n                .isEqualTo(FrodoParameterSpec.frodokem640aes.getName());\n    }\n\n    private static BCFrodoPublicKey createFrodoKem640AesPublicKey() {\n        FrodoPublicKeyParameters keyParameters = new FrodoPublicKeyParameters(\n                FrodoParameters.frodokem640aes,\n                createBytes(32, 11));\n        return new BCFrodoPublicKey(keyParameters);\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] createBytes(int size, int offset) {\n        byte[] bytes = new byte[size];\n        for (int index = 0; index < bytes.length; index++) {\n            bytes[index] = (byte) (index + offset);\n        }\n        return bytes;\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(BCFrodoPublicKey publicKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream out = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            out.writeObject(publicKey);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCFrodoPublicKey deserialize(byte[] serializedKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayInputStream bytes = new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedKey);\n        try (ObjectInputStream in = new ObjectInputStream(bytes)) {\n            return (BCFrodoPublicKey) in.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778130162821}]}
